weekend about there are
different conversations going on

24:39.278 --> 24:46.118 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
in the white community and the
black community and together,
but is there enough talking

24:46.118 --> 24:50.556 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
going on among people who may
disagree and may come together
as a result of what they're

24:50.556 --> 24:53.125 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
hearing from each other?

24:53.125 --> 24:58.263 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JULIAN ZELIZER: Well, listen,
the Black Lives Matter movement
has made incredible progress

24:58.263 --> 25:02.568 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
in bringing these issues on to
the table, combined with the
realities people see through

25:02.568 --> 25:05.604 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
the social media.

25:05.604 --> 25:11.610 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
But we do live in a very
fragmented political
environment, where, before this
issue, people

25:11.610 --> 25:17.182 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
