Dallas and how much difference

25:53.552 --> 25:55.621 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
will that make?

25:55.621 --> 25:57.790 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Reverend Jackson?

25:57.790 --> 26:01.393 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
REV. JESSE JACKSON: First of
all, the killer didn't come out
of the civil rights movement.

26:01.393 --> 26:05.764 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
That was a strategy alien
to the way we functioned.

26:05.764 --> 26:11.370 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Secondly, we need some real
renew -- there is a date,
November the 8th. And Trump has

26:11.370 --> 26:16.141 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
thrown down his gauntlet, saying
law and order, trying to imitate
Nixon.

26:16.141 --> 26:21.713 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We must choose reconciliation
over retaliation and revenge. I
hope President Obama will
address,

26:21.713 --> 26:27.786 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
underline the police issue, the
issue of jobs, jobs training and
economic reconstruction

26:27.786 --> 26:35.360 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and the race disparity. Race
disparity is real. It is real.
And it's growing.

26:35.360 --> 26:38.630 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: All right, we
are, unfortunately, out of time.
We hope to come back to all of

26:38.630 --> 26:41.667 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
you in the very near future.

26:41.667 --> 26:47.739 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Reverend Jackson, Mayor Kasim
Reed, DeRay McKesson, Julian
Zelizer, we thank you all.

26:47.739 --> 26:59.685 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JULIAN ZELIZER: Thank you.

26:59.685 --> 27:07.626 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Public debates
automatically turn political, as
the presidential campaigns enter

27:07.626 --> 27:11.163 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
their pre-conventional stretch.

27:11.163 --> 27:14.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Joining us, as they do every
Monday, to discuss the issues
that are shaping voters' choices

27:14.933 --> 27:20.172 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
are Tamara Keith of NPR and Amy
Walter of The Cook Political
Report.

27:20.172 --> 27:23.942 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Let's compare and assess what we
have seen happen in the last
several days. It's been

27:23.942 --> 27:30.415 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
an amazing period in our nation,
and we have seen the way Donald
Trump handled it. We saw

27:30.415 --> 27:34.286 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the way Hillary Clinton handled
it. How do you compare those two
things, Amy?

27:34.286 --> 27:37.789 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
AMY WALTER, The Cook Political
Report: Well, I think how I
think there is how they dealt

27:37.789 --> 27:43.595 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
with it in the immediate
aftermath, which was both were
very sort of nonpolitical. Both

27:43.595 --> 27:48.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
called for unity. Both called
for sort of ratcheting down the
rhetoric.

27:48.233 --> 27:53.005 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Today, though, you saw Donald
Trump talk a little bit more
about this. And if you had

27:53.005 --> 27:56.241 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to pick the difference of how
Donald Trump is talking about
this and Hillary Clinton

27:56.241 --> 28:02.047 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
is talking about this, she made
a talk at a church this weekend.
She talked about bringing

28:02.047 --> 28:07.452 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
America together. That's been
really the theme of her campaign
is bringing Americans together.

28:07.452 --> 28:13.625 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
What Donald Trump talked about
is how law and order is what
really -- is much more central

28:13.625 --> 28:19.765 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to his campaign. So one is
talking about the togetherness
of Americans. The other is
saying

28:19.765 --> 28:24.570 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the only way to keep us from
falling apart is to have strong
law and order.

28:24.570 --> 28:29.441 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It sounded very reminiscent of
another Republican presidential
candidate from 1968, which
was...

28:29.441 --> 28:30.075 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Richard Nixon.

28:30.075 --> 28:32.444 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
AMY WALTER: ... Richard Nixon.

28:32.444 --> 28:36.448 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Tam, it's not
insignificant where Hillary
Clinton chose to make these
comments.

28:36.448 --> 28:40.185 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
She was speaking at the
quadrennial Conference of
African Methodist Episcopal
Church.

28:40.185 --> 28:41.787 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
TAMARA KEITH, National
Public Radio: Right.

28:41.787 --> 28:45.123 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Obviously, we saw
Mother Emanuel AME Church in
Charleston was a member of that.

28:45.123 --> 28:49.061 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
So, she was speaking to an
audience which got this.

28:49.061 --> 28:53.131 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
At the same time, I was struck
when she said something like, we
have to learn, as white

28:53.131 --> 28:57.736 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
people, need to start listening
to black people, which shouldn't
be a shocking idea, but somehow

28:57.736 --> 28:58.737 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
it was taken as a big moment.

28:58.737 --> 29:00.939 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
TAMARA KEITH: Yes.

29:00.939 --> 29:04.843 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And the other interesting thing
about that is, it's not the
first time she's talk about

29:04.843 --> 29:09.181 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
that. It's not the first time
she's talked about talking to
white people about their

29:09.181 --> 29:14.353 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
privilege or about listening,
about walking in the shoes of
other people.

29:14.353 --> 29:20.993 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
This has actually been a theme
of her campaign for months now,
but, somehow, in that place,

29:20.993 --> 29:25.897 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
in this moment in time, it had a
different resonance than it's
had before. It got noticed.

29:25.897 --> 29:30.502 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: And, of course,
tomorrow, President Obama goes
to Dallas and we get to see him.

29:30.502 --> 29:33.171 align:left position:25%,start line:73.33% size:75%
I hate the term
consoler-in-chief again, because
he has to be that so often, but
that's what

29:33.171 --> 29:35.974 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
we see happen again.

29:35.974 --> 29:39.811 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Let's talk about what else is on
the candidates' minds right now,
which is, who's going to

29:39.811 --> 29:43.148 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
run with them? Who is going to
be on their ticket? We have
conventions coming right up.

29:43.148 --> 29:44.650 align:left position:25%,start line:86.67% size:75%
And are we any
closer to knowing?

29:44.650 --> 29:45.617 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
AMY WALTER: Do we have any idea?

29:45.617 --> 29:48.286 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
GWEN IFILL: Next week.

29:48.286 --> 29:52.124 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I'm terrible when it comes to
predicting who the vice
president is going to be. I'm
always

29:52.124 --> 29:57.029 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
wrong about this. And part of it
is, it's very difficult to
assess from here, and partly

29:57.029 --> 30:02.434 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
because we get so caught up in
the poll and the strategy and
who's going to fill the gaps.

30:02.434 --> 30:06.271 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And at the end of the day, this
is about -- I think sometimes
more important than anything

30:06.271 --> 30:07.706 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
else is the rapport
-- the rapport.

30:07.706 --> 30:10.075 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: The rapport. Yes.

30:10.075 --> 30:14.413 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
AMY WALTER: The rapport -- thank
you -- the chemistry that they
have between each other.

30:14.413 --> 30:19.017 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I think that that comes across
and it's even more important in
this day and age, where

30:19.017 --> 30:23.689 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
they're going to be together and
shot at every single angle,
live-streamed, Snapchatted,

30:23.689 --> 30:27.359 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
on television together. That is
going to come across and become
very important.

30:27.359 --> 30:31.196 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The other piece, as we're seeing
now, that these candidates are
literally trying their

30:31.196 --> 30:36.735 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
V.P.s out on the trail, on
television. Who succeeds and who
fails under the sharp microscope

30:36.735 --> 30:39.371 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
and under the spotlight?

30:39.371 --> 30:42.908 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Donald Trump now
today, he appeared with Chris
Christie. Not too long ago, he

30:42.908 --> 30:47.879 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
was with Mike Pence from
Indiana. He's basically trotting
them all out.

30:47.879 --> 30:51.483 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Does Hillary Clinton do the same
thing, or is she just waiting to
see what he does?

30:51.483 --> 30:55.854 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
TAMARA KEITH: Well, on Thursday,
she is campaigning with Senator
Tim Kaine of Virginia. And they

30:55.854 --> 30:58.323 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
