secretary, and probably five
other

31:24.449 --> 31:27.452 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
people who I'm not mentioning.

31:27.452 --> 31:30.655 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: That's what's
happening with Republicans.
They're putting out a whole list
of people

31:30.655 --> 31:34.192 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
who may or may not be vetted
right now. But are there other
goals besides that for this

31:34.192 --> 31:36.862 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
convention coming up?

31:36.862 --> 31:41.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
AMY WALTER: Well, the most
important goal, of course, for
Donald Trump is to make it

31:41.800 --> 31:45.570 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
at least appear as if there's
some unity in this party.

31:45.570 --> 31:49.975 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And the first hurdle he has to
overcome is this week as the
rules committee gets together.

31:49.975 --> 31:54.279 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
There's talk about that there's
going to be something of a never
Trump moment, where they

31:54.279 --> 31:56.848 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
can unbind delegates. I don't
think that's going to happen. In
fact, I am pretty convinced

31:56.848 --> 31:59.217 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
that's not going to happen.

31:59.217 --> 32:05.357 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But until that is actually over,
the talk will not die down. Once
he overcomes that

32:05.357 --> 32:08.593 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
hurdle, the next is, what does
this convention look like? There
obviously are a lot who aren't

32:08.593 --> 32:11.596 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
