phone every single day since
June 7.

33:26.872 --> 33:29.374 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
GWEN IFILL: Cute.
That's so high school.

33:29.374 --> 33:32.677 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But what about the platform
committee? They actually met,
and Bernie Sanders got a couple

33:32.677 --> 33:34.346 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
of things.

33:34.346 --> 33:38.383 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
TAMARA KEITH: Bernie Sanders got
a lot of what he was looking
for. The platform includes

33:38.383 --> 33:42.387 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
a $15 minimum wage, for
instance. Also, over the last
week or so, Hillary Clinton's
made

33:42.387 --> 33:45.323 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
a number of policy concessions.

33:45.323 --> 33:49.461 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
She's moved closer to Bernie
Sanders. She made some
announcements on health care, as

33:49.461 --> 33:56.134 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
well as college affordability.
So Bernie Sanders, you know,
this endorsement isn't for free.

33:56.134 --> 33:58.770 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Bernie Sanders has been pushing
Hillary Clinton, and you can
expect that to continue beyond

33:58.770 --> 33:59.537 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
tomorrow.

33:59.537 --> 34:03.208 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
GWEN IFILL: To the
extent platforms matter.

34:03.208 --> 34:05.443 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
AMY WALTER: Does a platform
matter, which they don't,
although I think -- good for
him.

34:05.443 --> 34:08.546 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
He got a lot of what he wanted.

34:08.546 --> 34:12.417 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The most fascinating thing about
this primary has not simply been
how Sanders has pushed

34:12.417 --> 34:16.321 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Hillary Clinton. I think it's
been twofold, one, how far she
has moved from the other

34:16.321 --> 34:21.393 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Clinton's legacy. Right. She is
really not running as a Bill
Clinton part two. She's

34:21.393 --> 34:23.828 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
running as a Hillary Clinton.

34:23.828 --> 34:27.499 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And she did something that Jeb
Bush and others didn't do, which
is she moved where the party

34:27.499 --> 34:30.035 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
went. Jeb Bush decided to stay
where his party was in the early
21st century.

34:30.035 --> 34:32.003 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
GWEN IFILL: OK.

34:32.003 --> 34:35.106 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We will see you wherever we are
at this time next week, waiting
probably still for more

34:35.106 --> 34:37.475 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
shoes to drop.

34:37.475 --> 34:44.616 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Amy Walter of The Cook Political
Report, Tamara Keith of NPR,
thank you both.

34:44.616 --> 34:50.322 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
TAMARA KEITH: You're welcome.

34:50.322 --> 34:55.260 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Stay with us.

34:55.260 --> 34:59.030 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Coming up on the "NewsHour," we
launch our series The End of
AIDS, starting with a look

34:59.030 --> 35:02.600 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
at an ambitious initiative
in San Francisco.

35:02.600 --> 35:08.740 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But, first: We reported all last
week on the fault lines between
Russia and the West over

35:08.740 --> 35:15.280 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the Russian-backed war in
Ukraine and Moscow's new,
aggressive posture against NATO.

35:15.280 --> 35:18.216 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Leaders of the North Atlantic
Treaty alliance met over the
weekend in Warsaw, and we go

35:18.216 --> 35:21.486 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
to John Yang for an update.

35:21.486 --> 35:25.357 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: With us now to
discuss what came out of the
NATO summit and the future of
the

35:25.357 --> 35:29.928 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
alliance is Esther Brimmer. She
has served in various roles at
the State Department.

35:29.928 --> 35:35.567 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Most recently, she was assistant
secretary of state for
international organization
affairs.

35:35.567 --> 35:39.137 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
She's now with the Council on
Foreign Relations and teaches at
George Washington University.

35:39.137 --> 35:42.540 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Esther Brimmer, thanks
for joining us.

35:42.540 --> 35:46.811 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
What would this -- this summit,
the president said it was the
most important moment for

35:46.811 --> 35:51.649 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
NATO since the end of the Cold
War. What were the big decisions
that came out of this meeting?

35:51.649 --> 35:54.819 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ESTHER BRIMMER, Former State
Department Official: Indeed,
this was an extremely important
summit.

35:54.819 --> 35:59.591 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
This was an opportunity for the
leaders to demonstrate that
there was real support and

35:59.591 --> 36:06.664 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
backing, concrete actions to
support the Eastern allies of
the alliance. What we saw were
that

36:06.664 --> 36:09.801 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the United States and other
important leaders within the
alliance are showing that they

36:09.801 --> 36:14.372 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
will commit troops
again to Europe.

36:14.372 --> 36:19.144 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We're seeing the deployment of
battalions in those countries
that are most threatened

36:19.144 --> 36:24.849 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
by the new tensions with Russia.
And it meant that the alliance
still matters, despite the

36:24.849 --> 36:28.353 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
turbulence created by the Brexit
vote in the European Union.

36:28.353 --> 36:30.989 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
JOHN YANG: Let's take
those one by one.

36:30.989 --> 36:36.327 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
First of all, the troops being
sent to Eastern Europe, troops
once again being deployed by

36:36.327 --> 36:42.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
NATO to deter Moscow, this is
sort of a return to the original
purpose of the alliance.

36:42.133 --> 36:44.502 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
ESTHER BRIMMER: Well, indeed.

36:44.502 --> 36:49.841 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The alliance is, of course, both
a political and a military
alliance to defend the territory

36:49.841 --> 36:56.781 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
of the NATO allies. And, once
again, we see that we need to
have a military presence in

36:56.781 --> 37:01.152 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Europe increased. As we know,
there has always been a U.S.
presence within Europe, which

37:01.152 --> 37:04.756 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
was happily reduced after
the end of the Cold War.

37:04.756 --> 37:08.760 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
However, now we see that
particularly the Baltic states
and others are concerned about

37:08.760 --> 37:15.366 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
their security, recognizing the
threats made by Russia against
those non-NATO countries

37:15.366 --> 37:20.805 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to their east. Importantly, we
see that, though, this is a
multilateral commitment. We see

37:20.805 --> 37:26.845 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
that countries of four nations
will lead the effort to station
rotating battalions in the

37:26.845 --> 37:30.615 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
eastern part of the
NATO countries.

37:30.615 --> 37:35.587 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, again, the United States,
but other countries, too, are
part of the response to show
that

37:35.587 --> 37:39.157 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the alliance as a whole is
committed to the territories of
those countries most under

37:39.157 --> 37:40.859 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
pressure.

37:40.859 --> 37:44.562 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JOHN YANG: You spoke also about
the British decision to leave
the European Union. What's

37:44.562 --> 37:46.197 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
that done to NATO?

37:46.197 --> 37:48.867 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
ESTHER BRIMMER: Indeed.

37:48.867 --> 37:53.404 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
As we know, that there are
important institutions in the
transatlantic relationship. The
North

37:53.404 --> 37:58.276 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Atlantic Treaty alliance, NATO,
has always been the underpinning
of that relationship.

37:58.276 --> 38:02.614 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But the European Union has an
important role in other types of
security, including border

38:02.614 --> 38:05.617 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
issues and others.

38:05.617 --> 38:10.822 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And so the relationship between
those countries are also part of
transatlantic security. The

38:10.822 --> 38:16.461 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
United Kingdom is really the
lynchpin. They're both members
of NATO and members of the
European

38:16.461 --> 38:19.864 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Union. They have an important
role to play. But they have a
sovereign choice about what

38:19.864 --> 38:24.002 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
they were going to do. The vote
for Brexit means that there is a
greater interest, I

38:24.002 --> 38:29.574 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
think, in the United Kingdom in
demonstrating their support for
the transatlantic alliance

38:29.574 --> 38:34.846 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and showing that they want to
continue to play an important
role as a key nation within

38:34.846 --> 38:37.482 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
the North Atlantic
Treaty Organization.

38:37.482 --> 38:42.020 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: And within Europe,
could NATO emerge as the
unifying force if E.U. is -- if
Britain

38:42.020 --> 38:44.622 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
leaves the E.U.?

38:44.622 --> 38:49.627 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ESTHER BRIMMER: They really play
two different roles, that the
NATO alliance is a military

38:49.627 --> 38:54.832 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
alliance. Its job is to provide
for the defense of the allies
who are part of it, yet it has

38:54.832 --> 38:58.870 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
a complementary role
to the European Union.

38:58.870 --> 39:04.909 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But NATO will also continue to
have its political role.
Ultimately, it is an alliance of
values

39:04.909 --> 39:07.879 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
based on the political values we
share. The United Kingdom will
be an important part of

39:07.879 --> 39:11.282 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
expressing and defending
those values.

39:11.282 --> 39:15.386 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And from what we see, they will
continue to want to demonstrate
their leadership in the

39:15.386 --> 39:18.790 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
alliance to demonstrate their
support for the transatlantic
relationship.

39:18.790 --> 39:23.895 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JOHN YANG: With the economic
uncertainty of leaving the
European Union, is it possible

39:23.895 --> 39:28.967 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
that Great Britain will no
longer keep up its -- it's one
of the few countries that

39:28.967 --> 39:33.571 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
is meeting its obligation in
defense spending among NATO
members. Is there a danger that

39:33.571 --> 39:36.107 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
that is going to stop?

39:36.107 --> 39:40.245 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ESTHER BRIMMER: There will be a
great deal of attention toward
seeing whether the United

39:40.245 --> 39:45.183 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Kingdom will be able to maintain
their financial commitment to
the alliance.

39:45.183 --> 39:51.489 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
As you have indicated, that of
the 28 members of the alliance,
only four have met the
commitment

39:51.489 --> 39:55.727 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
that was made, ironically, at
the last summit, which was held
in the United Kingdom in Wales,

39:55.727 --> 40:02.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
at which the allies committed to
paying 2 percent towards their
-- towards the alliance.

40:02.900 --> 40:05.536 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Only four countries meet that.

40:05.536 --> 40:09.941 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The United Kingdom is one of
them. Although the Cameron
government did institute
significant

40:09.941 --> 40:17.415 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
reductions in public spending in
recent years, they did recently
meet the 2 percent standard.

40:17.415 --> 40:20.251 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I think most allies are hoping
they will continue to do so, but
they will be under economic

40:20.251 --> 40:22.220 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
pressure. It will be a concern.

40:22.220 --> 40:23.421 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JOHN YANG: More interesting
days ahead for Europe.

40:23.421 --> 40:24.422 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
ESTHER BRIMMER: Indeed.

40:24.422 --> 40:26.858 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JOHN YANG: Esther Brimmer,
thanks for being with us.

40:26.858 --> 40:36.834 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
ESTHER BRIMMER: Thank
you very much.

40:36.834 --> 40:44.942 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Now we kick off a
special series about efforts to
try to end the AIDS epidemic.

40:44.942 --> 40:48.813 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Leaders and researchers from
around the globe will be meeting
at the International AIDS

40:48.813 --> 40:54.786 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Conference in South Africa next
week. One major focus, how to
stop the epidemic.

40:54.786 --> 40:59.257 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But with no vaccine or cure in
sight, how likely is that? This
week, we're looking at

40:59.257 --> 41:01.859 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
efforts around the world.

41:01.859 --> 41:06.831 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We start in San Francisco, where
we have followed people for the
past six months.

41:06.831 --> 41:10.335 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Correspondent William Brangham
and producer Jason Kane reported
this series, with the

41:10.335 --> 41:15.273 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
support of the Pulitzer
Center on Crisis Reporting.

41:15.273 --> 41:22.680 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: San
Francisco's gay pride events
went off this summer like they
usually

41:22.680 --> 41:27.719 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
do, loud and colorful
and celebratory.

41:27.719 --> 41:32.523 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But there's additional reason to
celebrate. San Francisco, one of
the cities where the

41:32.523 --> 41:36.327 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
AIDS epidemic first emerged, and
one that suffered terribly from
it, has now launched

41:36.327 --> 41:39.630 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the country's most ambitious
campaign to control it.

41:39.630 --> 41:43.835 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
It's called Getting to Zero.

41:43.835 --> 41:50.608 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Luis Canales is a living example
of that campaign. Canales is
HIV-positive. He got infected
having

41:50.608 --> 41:55.980 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
unprotected sex with another man
three years ago. But -- and this
is one of the linchpins

41:55.980 --> 41:59.784 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
of San Francisco's effort --
Canales was tested and then
started on HIV treatment
immediately

41:59.784 --> 42:01.986 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
after diagnosis.

42:01.986 --> 42:05.857 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LUIS CANALES, AIDS Patient: Yes,
right away. And I think it was
the next day, I came in

42:05.857 --> 42:07.925 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
and started my meds.

42:07.925 --> 42:10.361 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DR. STEVEN DEEKS, University of
California, San Francisco: That,
as a physician is my

42:10.361 --> 42:13.064 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
goal, to keep people on
therapy for their own good.

42:13.064 --> 42:14.866 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: Steven
Deeks is Canales' doctor.

42:14.866 --> 42:15.800 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
DR. STEVEN DEEKS:
Luis, how you doing?

42:15.800 --> 42:17.135 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
LUIS CANALES: Pretty good.

42:17.135 --> 42:19.737 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: This
approach is called Rapid.

42:19.737 --> 42:23.574 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And Deeks says, the sooner the
virus can be stopped with
antiretroviral drugs, the
better,

42:23.574 --> 42:26.744 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
but it's not just
for the patient.

42:26.744 --> 42:30.848 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DR. STEVEN DEEKS: From a public
health perspective -- and I
think this is what's really
driving

42:30.848 --> 42:34.352 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
a lot of interest in the RAPID
program -- someone's on therapy,
they can't pass the virus to
other

42:34.352 --> 42:36.287 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
people.

42:36.287 --> 42:41.259 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: Dr. Diane
Havlir of U.C. San Francisco
pushed the city to embrace RAPID

42:41.259 --> 42:44.562 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
treatment years before other
cities did. She's also one of
the architects of the entire
Getting

42:44.562 --> 42:48.966 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
to Zero plan.

42:48.966 --> 42:52.837 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
She says the idea that treatment
should wait because of cost, or
side effects, or fear

42:52.837 --> 42:55.206 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
people won't stick
with it is outdated.

42:55.206 --> 42:57.542 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DR. DIANE HAVLIR, University of
California, San Francisco: If
you have heart attack, you

42:57.542 --> 43:01.612 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
do need to take medicines for
your heart, in most cases for
life. We don't say, how

43:01.612 --> 43:04.582 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
do you feel about this? Do you
want to go home? We say, you
need to start these medicines

43:04.582 --> 43:08.186 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
now. This is a serious
condition. It's the same with
HIV.

43:08.186 --> 43:11.489 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: Widespread
testing and treatment for HIV is
considered the single best way

43:11.489 --> 43:14.992 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
to curtail this epidemic.

43:14.992 --> 43:19.263 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Treatment prevents infected
people from progressing to AIDS,
and it reduces the likelihood
that

43:19.263 --> 43:24.135 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
they will infect others. The
Getting to Zero campaign wants
to cut those new HIV infections

43:24.135 --> 43:29.740 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
in the city by 90 percent by
2020. That would mean cutting
them from 300 a year now down

43:29.740 --> 43:34.712 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to about 30. They also want to
cut HIV deaths by a similar
percentage, from about 150 a

43:34.712 --> 43:37.982 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
year today down to just 15.

43:37.982 --> 43:45.323 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They want to get both down to
zero by 2030. Of course, the
best way to stop HIV is to

43:45.323 --> 43:48.326 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
stop people getting infected in
the first place, so San
Francisco is aggressively
promoting

43:48.326 --> 43:51.128 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
its prevention strategy.

43:51.128 --> 43:53.464 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Jason Lloyd is a 41-year-old
gay man in San Francisco.

43:53.464 --> 43:54.799 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
MAN: Your first and last name?

43:54.799 --> 43:56.801 align:left position:25%,start line:86.67% size:75%
JASON LLOYD, San
Francisco: Jason Lloyd.

43:56.801 --> 44:01.172 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: He doesn't
have HIV. And to stay that way,
back in January, he was

44:01.172 --> 44:06.177 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
about to start taking what's
called PrEP, pre-exposure
prophylaxis. It's a daily dose

44:06.177 --> 44:09.747 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
of the drug Truvada that will
greatly reduce his chance of
infection if he's exposed to

44:09.747 --> 44:11.716 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
HIV.

44:11.716 --> 44:16.954 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JASON LLOYD: There is always in
the back of my head when I go to
get tested, is this going

44:16.954 --> 44:20.892 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to be -- is the test going to
come back positive? Because I do
have risky activity, although

44:20.892 --> 44:24.161 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
it might be low-risk,
still risky.

44:24.161 --> 44:29.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: Truvada was
approved as a prevention tool by
the FDA in 2012. Despite

44:29.433 --> 44:34.171 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
its proven ability to prevent
HIV, it's been very
controversial, and it hasn't
been widely

44:34.171 --> 44:38.476 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
embraced elsewhere. Some fear
those who take it will engage in
riskier behavior, though

44:38.476 --> 44:42.346 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
there's very little
evidence of that occurring.

44:42.346 --> 44:46.951 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Right now, an estimated 6,000
people in San Francisco are
taking Truvada for HIV
prevention,

44:46.951 --> 44:49.320 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
and Jason Lloyd is
joining their ranks.

44:49.320 --> 44:52.356 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JASON LLOYD: And so I will start
taking it tonight. So, we will
see.

44:52.356 --> 44:58.696 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: Of course,
Truvada is for those who are
uninfected. Keeping those who

44:58.696 --> 45:05.870 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
are infected healthy and linked
to care is another main thrust
of San Francisco's plan.

45:05.870 --> 45:09.307 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Max Ruben works for San
Francisco's Public Health
Department. For months, he's
been making

45:09.307 --> 45:13.344 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
regular visits to see an
HIV-positive man named Barry
Stover.

45:13.344 --> 45:16.380 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MAX RUBEN, San Francisco Public
Health Department: Barry.
Morning, bud. How's it going?

45:16.380 --> 45:22.920 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
BARRY STOVER, HIV Patient: I
found out I had HIV. I was ready
to kill myself, but I didn't.

45:22.920 --> 45:27.925 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: Stover was
diagnosed in 2015 after years of
living on the streets,

45:27.925 --> 45:32.797 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
addicted to drugs. He's still
using today, and the first few
times we met him, he was

45:32.797 --> 45:38.035 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
supposed to be taking his daily
HIV medications, but it wasn't
clear that was happening.

45:38.035 --> 45:44.241 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
BARRY STOVER: I try to take 'em,
but I just don't like taking
pills.

45:44.241 --> 45:48.179 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: After their
visit, Ruben walked Stover to
one of the city's health

45:48.179 --> 45:52.883 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
clinics. With regular visits,
they hope he will be more
consistent with his medications.

45:52.883 --> 45:57.355 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DR. DIANE HAVLIR: No one is
proposing that every single
person with HIV gets a daily

45:57.355 --> 46:03.761 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
visit. However, if we want to
fully control the epidemic, we
are going to need to do that

46:03.761 --> 46:08.065 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
for some people, and it's
completely justified. It's
either pay now or pay later.

46:08.065 --> 46:11.369 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: A few blocks
away, Kenneth Grosenbach and his
girlfriend Michele Campbell

46:11.369 --> 46:15.006 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
are trying to stay on their
medications as well.

46:15.006 --> 46:20.111 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He's HIV-positive. She isn't.
Because he's taking his meds,
she's far less likely to

46:20.111 --> 46:25.816 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
get infected. She's also taking
PrEP, which gives her even more
protection.

46:25.816 --> 46:30.855 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It's hard to convey just how
brutal Kenny Grosenbach's life
has been so far. Born to

46:30.855 --> 46:36.193 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
a teenage rape victim, he was
abandoned when he was 10. He
says he's been selling sex and

46:36.193 --> 46:41.265 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
addicted to drugs for the last
20 years Grosenbach admits he's
had trouble in the past staying

46:41.265 --> 46:45.970 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
on his HIV medication, but now
he says he's got a reason to
stay alive.

46:45.970 --> 46:49.240 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
KENNETH GROSENBACH, HIV Patient:
What encouraged me to get my
medicine, and start my medicine,

46:49.240 --> 46:53.344 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
is that I found somebody that I
really care about. I found
somebody that cares about me.

46:53.344 --> 46:57.081 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MICHELE CAMPBELL, San Francisco:
Now that we're together and we
want to start a normal

46:57.081 --> 47:00.051 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
life, we need to start
doing normal things.

47:00.051 --> 47:05.189 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: To stop the
AIDS epidemic, two years ago,
the U.N. set an ambitious goal,

47:05.189 --> 47:09.293 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and it's one that we're seeing
implemented here in San
Francisco. It's to get 90
percent

47:09.293 --> 47:13.364 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
of HIV-positive people tested,
90 percent of them onto
treatment, and 90 percent of

47:13.364 --> 47:17.334 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
them to have their virus
fully suppressed.

47:17.334 --> 47:20.404 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Whether that's achievable and
whether that'll stem the
epidemic is still an open
question.

47:20.404 --> 47:24.742 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The challenge of hitting those
targets became clearer when we
returned to the city three

47:24.742 --> 47:26.377 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
months later.

47:26.377 --> 47:29.180 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
WOMAN: What is the reason to
see the pharmacist tomorrow?

47:29.180 --> 47:33.350 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
KENNETH GROSENBACH: Because I
have zero medicines. Yes, I need
my medicine.

47:33.350 --> 47:36.654 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: Kenny
Grosenbach is now homeless. He'd
just been kicked out of his

47:36.654 --> 47:40.925 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
place, and he stopped
taking his HIV medication.

47:40.925 --> 47:46.897 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
KENNETH GROSENBACH: I have to
say that these few months have
been hard. I went completely

47:46.897 --> 47:52.570 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
backwards. I am not really being
too much on the responsible end
for my meds or for

47:52.570 --> 47:58.476 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
my relationship. I am just
trying to make it day by day.

47:58.476 --> 48:03.447 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: "Science"
magazine's Jon Cohen, who's
covered HIV/AIDS for more than

48:03.447 --> 48:07.618 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
25 years, and who helped us
report this series, says Kenny
Grosenbach is a testament to
just

48:07.618 --> 48:10.788 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
how hard it's going to be to
achieve the U.N.'s targets.

48:10.788 --> 48:14.825 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JON COHEN, "Science": Who are
these people who are so hard to
test, who are so hard to

48:14.825 --> 48:22.399 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
link to care, and who are so
hard to get suppressed? Kenny's
that guy.

48:22.399 --> 48:28.072 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He's really tough on every level
for the health care system. He
knows his status. Linking

48:28.072 --> 48:34.011 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
him to care, he's been linked to
care, but keeping him virally
suppressed? Well, he has

48:34.011 --> 48:38.149 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
a really hard time staying on
his medication. And it ties back
to housing, right? I mean,

48:38.149 --> 48:41.519 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
this is a guy who's
living on the streets.

48:41.519 --> 48:46.857 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: But for most
people, the Getting to Zero
campaign has been working.

48:46.857 --> 48:51.028 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
This summer, six months after we
first met him, Jason Lloyd was
still taking the PrEP

48:51.028 --> 48:56.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
drug, Truvada. He said some of
his friends take it, too. They
help remind him to take

48:56.100 --> 49:00.204 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
his, and it's all becoming very
normal-seeming. We caught up
with him as he was getting made

49:00.204 --> 49:05.709 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
up for one of his drag
performances. His stage name is
Beyonda, Beyonda Mazing.

49:05.709 --> 49:10.114 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And contrary to the critics'
fears about taking Truvada, the
pill hadn't turned him into a

49:10.114 --> 49:13.951 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
wild risk-taker. In fact, he'd
been having a bit of a dry
spell.

49:13.951 --> 49:17.521 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JASON LLOYD: I'm actually having
less sex since I started taking
Truvada than before.

49:17.521 --> 49:22.626 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Yes, I feel more like a Truvada
monk than a Truvada whore.

49:22.626 --> 49:25.696 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: Luis Canales
has also been taking his
medication consistently, and
he's

49:25.696 --> 49:27.631 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
had no side effects.

49:27.631 --> 49:30.868 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LUIS CANALES: Meds every day.
Whenever any of my doctors need
to see me, I go in and

49:30.868 --> 49:33.337 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
see them.

49:33.337 --> 49:37.875 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: Partly because
of how quickly he was put on
treatment, extensive tests
cannot

49:37.875 --> 49:41.645 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
find the virus anywhere in his
body. And doctors are now
studying him to see if they can
learn

49:41.645 --> 49:45.616 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
any clues about how
to cure people.

49:45.616 --> 49:49.153 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
And across town at Barry
Stover's place, more good news.
After struggling to stick with

49:49.153 --> 49:51.388 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
his meds, Stover's
been doing it.

49:51.388 --> 49:53.257 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
BARRY STOVER: I'm
undetectable, so...

49:53.257 --> 49:55.025 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM:
You're undetectable?

49:55.025 --> 49:58.262 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
BARRY STOVER: Yes. That's what
-- what my doctor said, so...

49:58.262 --> 49:59.029 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM:
Congratulations.

49:59.029 --> 50:00.531 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
BARRY STOVER: Yes.

50:00.531 --> 50:02.299 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM:
That's a big deal.

50:02.299 --> 50:05.035 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
BARRY STOVER: Yes.

50:05.035 --> 50:09.306 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: But things
just keep spiraling down for
Kenny Grosenbach and Michele
Campbell.

50:09.306 --> 50:12.943 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They are both homeless now. She
was kicked out of her place. And
both are completely

50:12.943 --> 50:15.512 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
off their medications.

50:15.512 --> 50:20.184 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
HIV is likely replicating
rapidly in Kenny's immune cells,
and because Campbell is off

50:20.184 --> 50:22.820 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Truvada, she's at high
risk of infection.

50:22.820 --> 50:26.757 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
They said the main thing they
focus on now is their addiction.

50:26.757 --> 50:31.996 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MICHELE CAMPBELL: It seems like
since we have been out on the
streets. Getting high has

50:31.996 --> 50:34.965 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
been, like, the priority, just
because we just forget about
everything else.

50:34.965 --> 50:36.533 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
KENNETH GROSENBACH: You
don't have to feel at all.

50:36.533 --> 50:40.571 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MICHELE CAMPBELL: I really just
want to get off the drugs, and
start taking medication,

50:40.571 --> 50:47.044 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and start living our life and
actually be happy, because this
is miserable out here.

50:47.044 --> 50:52.383 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: San Francisco
is still a few years away from
its Getting to Zero target.

50:52.383 --> 50:57.121 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Despite the struggles they face,
Dr. Diane Havlir remains
optimistic they will get there.

50:57.121 --> 51:00.891 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DR. DIANE HAVLIR: The worst
thing that you can do is fail,
but, if you don't try at all,

51:00.891 --> 51:06.463 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
you're never going to have the
chance of succeeding. So,
obstacles and barriers for me
are just

51:06.463 --> 51:09.767 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
part of the journey
and don't deter me.

51:09.767 --> 51:13.404 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: Even as the
city cheers its advances, the
difficulty of bringing the

51:13.404 --> 51:17.241 align:left position:25%,start line:86.67% size:75%
AIDS epidemic to
an end is obvious.

51:17.241 --> 51:22.046 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Public health officials say,
after nearly 35 years since the
epidemic surfaced, the

51:22.046 --> 51:27.284 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
world has never had this many
proven tools so close at hand to
fight HIV. But putting

51:27.284 --> 51:31.755 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
those tools to work for everyone
remains the challenge going
forward.

51:31.755 --> 51:34.625 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
For the "PBS NewsHour," I'm
William Brangham in San
Francisco.

51:34.625 --> 51:39.029 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
